Pre-heat oven to 375 degrees F. Bring a large pot of water to a boil, season with salt. Combine butternut squash with 2 tablespoons of olive oil in a medium mixing bowl, season with salt and pepper. Arrange squash in single layer on a sheet pan. Roast for about 20 minutes or until nice and brown. Saute onions in a large skillet over medium heat with remaining olive oil, about 3-4 minutes or until opaque. Add butternut squash and cherry tomatoes. Cook pasta according to the package directions; reserve one cup of the cooking water. Add cooking water to the sauce, bring to a simmer. Drain pasta and toss it with the sauce. Remove skillet from the flame, top with cheese and crispy kale before serving.